2026-04-16 12:27:50 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Ambient sensor module relay contact set / immediate output wiring'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show: (1) PSU output and control module input are at full ~12 V; (2) relay coil is correctly driven; (3) the relay common contact in the ambient sensor module sits at the full input voltage (~11.99 V); but (4) the relay switched output contact is only at ~0.36 V while connected to the load, and the same low voltage appears at the load module input. This localizes a large, unintended voltage drop across the relay contact itself or the very short wiring from that contact to the output terminals. The load and its series diode behave normally at the reduced voltage, and the previously tested indicator/ground circuitry is good. Therefore the root cause is a high‑resistance / intermittently opening relay output contact (or its immediate solder joint / trace) in the ambient sensor module, which limits current and causes the lamp to lose proper supply, manifesting as the brief periodic off behavior.'
